---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Azure Foundry Agent Chat">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About Azure Foundry Agent Chat</h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          Azure Foundry Agent Chat is a modern web application built with Astro that provides a user-friendly interface to interact with Azure Foundry Agent services.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Real-time chat interface with Azure Foundry agents</li>
          <li>Secure authentication with Azure Active Directory</li>
          <li>Markdown support for rich text responses</li>
          <li>Built with modern web technologies</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Technologies</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Astro, React, TailwindCSS</li>
          <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Microsoft Authentication Library (MSAL)</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Azure Static Web Apps</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Getting Started</h2>
        <p>
          To use this application, you'll need:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>An Azure account with access to Foundry Agent services</li>
          <li>Proper permissions and credentials for authentication</li>
        </ol>
        
        <p class="mt-4">
          Simply navigate to the Chat page, sign in with your Azure credentials, and start interacting with the AI agents!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
